      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MADAM HONKY TONK (3) was a big winner two back scoring by one length then got further back last time but came home hard into third and beaten 7 lengths at this track (18.79). Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in two starts. Rates highly and will give a great sight. SCOTT SHENANIGAN (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind All Things Go (18.51) in a Grade 5. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Expected to be in this for a long way. CHATTAHOOCHE (7) was midfield throughout and finished there last time when 5th (22.68) at Shepparton. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. SANDY BALE (2) has strong claims after a close top-three finish last time out.",
